Waorani People win landmark legal victory against Ecuadorian Government
       A key legal precedent for indigenous rights and rainforest
       protection in a major setback for Ecuadorian Government’s plans to
       drill for oil across 7 million acres of South-Central Ecuadorian
       Amazon.
